<!--

Notes
=========

When JS is turned off the navigation should be present as an expanded list of links.

When CSS is turned off the navigation should be presented as a set of nested unordered links under section headings, styled only in basic HTML.

Aria landmark role of "navigation" needs to be added to both the nav elements.

Aria landmark role of "banner" needs to be added to the header  .

There should be an invisible (recommended) "Skip main navigation" link which is the first thing you tab to on a page.

Section
----
The navigation section should have a hidden h2 of "main navigation" (webaim.org).

Icons
----
Icons that require text should be read out by including a span containing the description that is set to visually-hidden.
Icons that are non-description (such as arrows) should be hidden and not read out.


Search
----
Aria landmark role of "search" should be added to the form controlling the search functionality.
Placeholder should be HTML5.
The search form should be either visible or visually-hidden and connected to the input box with for/name.

-->

